<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="93" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="93">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Sexual state</emphasis>
not observed. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Conidiophores</emphasis>
macronematous, synnematous, 200-350 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
including conidiogenous apparatus, synnemata frequently swollen at the base, frequently wider at the stipe, brown to light brown, expanding branches at the apex, (15
<normalizedToken originalValue="–)35–45(–">-)35-45(-</normalizedToken>
70) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
in width. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Conidiogenous cells</emphasis>
discrete, terminal, percurrent and phialidic proliferation, hyaline, cylindrical,(10
<normalizedToken originalValue="–)14–17(–">-)14-17(-</normalizedToken>
19) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-3 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Conidia</emphasis>
hyaline, one-celled, cylindrical to obovoid, (5.1
<normalizedToken originalValue="–)6.5–7.8(–">-)6.5-7.8(-</normalizedToken>
10.5) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2.1-3.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Cultural characteristics</emphasis>
: Colonies on OA, hyaline at first, later becoming olivaceous in the center, hyphae hyaline, appressed and immersed, aerial mycelium frequently present on wood tissue, synnemata abundant in WA cultures, Optimal growth temperature on MEA is 25 °C with radial growth rate 6.0 (
<normalizedToken originalValue="±">+/-</normalizedToken>
0.5) mm/d, growth slightly reduced at 10 °C and 35 °C.
</paragraph>
